'''Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group: Mounded Tombs of Ancient Japan''' ({{lang|ja|百舌鳥・古市古墳群 -古代日本の墳墓群-}}) is a collective name for 45 kofun located in {{ill|Sakai|ja|堺市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakai|qq=}}, {{ill|Habikino|ja|羽曳野市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Habikino|qq=}}, and {{ill|Fujiidera|ja|藤井寺市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiidera|qq=}}, Osaka Prefecture, Japan. These tumuli are categorized into the {{ill|Mozu Kofun Group|ja|百舌鳥古墳群|1=Mozu Tombs|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mozu Kofun Group|13=User:Immanuelle/Mozu Tombs|qq=}} and {{ill|Furuichi Kofun Cluster|lt=Furuichi Kofun Cluster|lt=Furuichi Kofun Group|ja|古市古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furuichi Kofun Group|qq=}}. The site was officially designated as a World Cultural Heritage Site during the {{ill|43rd World Heritage Committee|ja|第43回世界遺産委員会|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/43rd World Heritage Committee|qq=}} meeting on {{ill|July 6, 2019|ja|2019th year 7月6日|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/July 6, 2019|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mainichi.jp/articles/20190706/k00/00m/040/180000c|title=Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group designated as World Heritage Site|publisher=Mainichi Shimbun|accessdate=2019-07-06}}</ref>
== Background and Preservation == === Nomination for World Heritage Listing === Efforts to nominate the Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group as a World Heritage Site began in 2007 when it was proposed to {{ill|Agency for Cultural Affairs (Japan)|ja|文化庁|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Agency for Cultural Affairs (Japan)|qq=}}. After being included in Japan's tentative list in 2008, it was officially submitted to UNESCO in 2010.<ref>{{Cite book|title=World Heritage Yearbook 2009|publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs|date=2009}}</ref>
=== Preservation Measures === As many kofun are classified as {{ill|Imperial Mausoleum Reference Land|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Mausoleum Reference Land|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=}} under the jurisdiction of the Imperial Household Agency, protection under the {{ill|Cultural Properties Protection Law|ja|文化財保護法|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Cultural Properties Protection Law|qq=}} is limited. Instead, preservation measures include restrictions on construction and landscape design under urban planning laws.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mozu-furuichi.jp/jp/conference/headquarters_nine_dl/gidai01.pdf|title=Preservation Measures for Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group|accessdate=2021-05-09}}</ref>
== Composition == The site comprises 45 kofun in three cities, dating from the late 4th to 5th centuries.
=== Notable Tumuli in the Mozu Area === * {{ill|Daisen Kofun|ja|大仙陵古墳|1=Daisenryō Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daisen Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Daisenryō Kofun|qq=}}: Japan's largest kofun, believed to be the tomb of {{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仁徳天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Nintoku|qq=}}. * {{ill|Nagayama Kofun|ja|永山古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagayama Kofun|qq=}}: Accompanying tumulus associated with the Daisen Kofun.
=== Notable Tumuli in the Furuichi Area === * {{ill|Konda Gobyo-yama Kofun|ja|誉田御廟山古墳|1=Konda Gobyoyama Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konda Gobyo-yama Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Konda Gobyoyama Kofun|qq=}}: Believed to be the tomb of {{ill|Emperor Ojin|ja|応神天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Ojin|qq=}}. * {{ill|Nakatsuyama Kofun|ja|仲津山古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatsuyama Kofun|qq=}}: Attributed to {{ill|Nakatsuhime|lt=Empress Nakatsuhime|ja|仲姫命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatsuhime|qq=}}.
== Related Information == * {{ill|Agency for Cultural Affairs (Japan)|ja|文化庁|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Agency for Cultural Affairs (Japan)|qq=}} official page for Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group: [http://www.mozu-furuichi.jp/] * {{Cite book|title=Mozu-Furuichi Kofun Group: Heritage and Preservation|author=Sakai City Cultural Property Division|year=2019}}
